markdown: Lela Evangeline Booher Vita Born, 9 March 1898, at Dayton, Ohio. Educated at: Ohio State University, B.S., 1920 Iowa, M.S., 1922 Columbia University, Ph. D. (Chemistry) 1928. Positions held include: Instructor in Biochemistry, New York Post-Graduate Medical School and Hospital, 1922-1924. Assistant in Chemistry, Columbia University, 1924-1928. Biochemist, St. Luke's Hospital, Cleveland, Ohio, 1928-1929. Instructor in Chemistry, Columbia University, 1930-1936. Chief, Foods and Nutrition, Bureau of Home Economics, USDA, 1936 to about 1942. Chemist, Children's Hospital, Milwaukee, Wisconsin, 1942-1943. Nutritionist, General Mills, Inc., Laboratories, Minneapolis, Minnesota, about 1943-1951. Consultant, Self-employed, Tucson, Arizona, 1951 to the present, 1972. Charter Member, American Institute of Nutrition, 1933, on; Member, the American Society of Biological Chemists, and of other profesional societies in the field of chemistry and nutrition. Member at various times of committees, editorial boards and the like. Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/ztwd0227
